<li>As dimerization and inducer recognition are the only activities known to be associated with the Nterminal domain of MelR , we conclude that alanine substitution of the three cysteine residues in this region of MelR had no effect on the function of the protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12675795" target="_blank">12675795</a>]<br></li>
