<li>b-Galactosidase expression was measured in cells containing pJW15 that encodes MelR ( + MelR : black ﬁlled bars ) , or the control pJWDmelR with no melR insert ( MelR : open bars ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18346968" target="_blank">18346968</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>Interestingly , some of the gene expressions are controlled by cAMP-CAP , such as malFG , malKM , lamB , melAB ( through MelR ) and glpF , suggesting that Era-dE overproduction affects the carbon source metabolism .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12125819" target="_blank">12125819</a>]<br></li>
<li>From our study , we can conclude that , though the ligandfree forms of both E. coli AraC and MelR proteins strongly repress expression from their own promoters , different mechanisms are used for ligand-dependent switching to a state that can activate transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16621812" target="_blank">16621812</a>]<br></li>
<li>INTRODUCTION MelR protein in Escherichia coli is a transcription activator required for the expression of the melAB operon ( Webster et al. , 1989 ) , which encodes proteins essential for melibiose metabolism ( Hanatani et al. , 1984 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1445207" target="_blank">1445207</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of the E. coli K-12 melAB genes , which encode products essential for melibiose metabolism , depends on transcription activation by MelR and CRP , and is triggered by melibiose ( 7,9 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18346968" target="_blank">18346968</a>]<br></li>
<li>MelR is essential for induction of the melAB operon that is responsible for melibiose metabolism .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10760179" target="_blank">10760179</a>]<br></li>
<li>ChbR and ChbF are paralogues of MelR , the repressor of the E. coli melibiose operon , and melA , the α-galactosidase of the melibiose operon , respectively ( Parker and Hall , 1990a ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11361063" target="_blank">11361063</a>]<br></li>
<li>MelR activates expression of the melA and melB genes , encoding an α-galactosidase and a melibiose permease , respectively .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12060687" target="_blank">12060687</a>]<br></li>
<li>Published online 16 March 2008 Autoregulation of the Escherichia coli melR promoter : repression involves four molecules of MelR Shivanthi Samarasinghe , Mohamed Samir El-Robh , David C. Grainger , 1 1 1 Wenke Zhang , Panos Soultanas and Stephen J. W. Busby * 2 2 1 , Received December 20 , 2007 ; Revised February 29 , 2008 ; Accepted March 3 , 2008 ABSTRACT The Escherichia coli MelR protein is a transcription activator that autoregulates its own promoter by repressing transcription initiation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18346968" target="_blank">18346968</a>]<br></li>
<li>We previously showed that expression from pmelAB is not affected by large changes in melR gene dosage ( Webster et al. , 1987 , 1989 ) ; thus it is unlikely that our measurements are distorted by small changes in MelR expression resulting from mutations in pJW12 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1445207" target="_blank">1445207</a>]<br></li>
<li>Finally , the third line of data shows an important control ; expression in every case is minimal in the absence of MelR and CRP alone is unable to activate the melAB promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10760178" target="_blank">10760178</a>]<br></li>
<li>MelR binds to lates its own expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10760179" target="_blank">10760179</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this paper , we present a study of similar complex repression by a transcription factor that is related to AraC , the E. coli K-12 MelR protein , which represses transcription of its own gene , melR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18346968" target="_blank">18346968</a>]<br></li>
<li>At the pmelR promoter , MelR binds at site R , centred just downstream of the transcription start point , and represses its own transcription ( 19 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12060687" target="_blank">12060687</a>]<br></li>
<li>The observation that the melAB promoter is positively rather than negatively controlled ( Webster et al. , 1987 ) strongly suggested that meiR encodes a transcription activator , and this was corroborated by the discovery of sequence similarities between MelR and the well-characterized arabinose operon activator , AraC ( Henikoff et al. , 1989 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1445207" target="_blank">1445207</a>]<br></li>
<li>The meiR and melAB genes are transcribed from divergent promoters ( Webster et al. , 1987 ) : expression from the meiR promoter ( pmelR ) is dependent on the cyclic AMP receptor protein ( Webster et al. , 1988 ) , whereas the melAB promoter ( pmelAB ) is dependent on MelR binding at two sites located upstream of the melAB transcription start ( Fig. 1 ) ( Webster et al. , 1989 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1445207" target="_blank">1445207</a>]<br></li>
<li>The MelR regulator controls transcription from the melAB operon promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9409145" target="_blank">9409145</a>]<br></li>
<li>Summary The Escherichia coli MelR protein is a transcription activator that , in the presence of melibiose , activates expression of the melAB operon by binding to four sites located just upstream of the melAB promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10760179" target="_blank">10760179</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of MelR is controlled by the melR promoter , which drives initiation of a divergent transcript from 237-bp upstream of the melAB transcript start point ( 10,11 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18346968" target="_blank">18346968</a>]<br></li>
<li>MelR is encoded by the melR gene , which is expressed from a divergent transcript that starts 237 bp upstream of the melAB promoter transcript start point .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10760179" target="_blank">10760179</a>]<br></li>
<li>moter in vivo is dependent on melibiose and MelR , the melR gene product that is encoded by the nt sequence upstream from meL4 and transcribed divergently from the melAB promoter ( Webster et al. , 1987 ; 1988 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2684786" target="_blank">2684786</a>]<br></li>
<li>MelR is encoded by the melR gene that is located upstream from the melAB promoter ( Webster et al. , 1987 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10760179" target="_blank">10760179</a>]<br></li>
<li>MelR is encoded by the melR gene , which is located immediately upstream of the melA gene .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10760178" target="_blank">10760178</a>]<br></li>
<li>MelR is encoded by the melR gene , which is located immediately upstream of the melA gene , and transcribed from a promoter that is divergent from the melAB promoter ( the transcription start points of the melAB and melR promoters are 237 bases apart ; see Fig. 1 ) ( 9 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10747919" target="_blank">10747919</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the absence of melibiose , MelR is unable to activate the melAB promoter but autoregulates its own expression by repressing the melR promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16621812" target="_blank">16621812</a>]<br></li>
<li>In this situation , MelR autoregulates its own expression by binding to site R and repressing its own promoter , and this repression is reinforced by upstream binding of MelR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18346968" target="_blank">18346968</a>]<br></li>
<li>Note that , in pJWI2 , melR is constitutively expressed from the gatP2 promoter and there is no autoregulation of MelR expression ( Webster et al. , 1988 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1445207" target="_blank">1445207</a>]<br></li>
<li>The melR promoter and its repression by MelR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18346968" target="_blank">18346968</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18346968" target="_blank">18346968</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , the melR promoter is not eficiently repressed by MelR , and MelR is over-expressed .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18346968" target="_blank">18346968</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , the melR promoter is not efficiently repressed by MelR and MelR is overexpressed .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10760179" target="_blank">10760179</a>]<br></li>
